[49m[39m  366, 366[0m:[39m[49m If you skip evaluation, you're deploying a policy trained in simulation without any evidence it works in reality.
[0m[49m[39m  367, 367[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      368[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **A note on OPE methodology for clinical settings:** The importance sampling approach shown below is simplified for illustration. In practice, behavior policy estimation (estimating the probability the historical operator took each action) requires a separate modeling step, typically a supervised classifier trained on the same historical data. Without good behavior policy estimates, importance weights are unreliable.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      369[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      370[0m:[38;5;10m[49m For high-stakes domains like hospital operations, you should use multiple OPE estimators and compare them: basic importance sampling, per-decision importance sampling (PDIS), and doubly-robust methods that combine a learned reward model with importance weighting to reduce variance. If the estimators disagree substantially, that's a signal you don't yet have enough data or your behavior policy model is poor.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      371[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      372[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Weight clipping (capping individual importance weights at some maximum, typically 5-10x) is essential for variance reduction. Without clipping, a single trajectory where the behavior and evaluation policies diverge sharply can dominate the entire estimate. The bootstrap confidence interval shown below is also unreliable for weighted estimators; prefer the asymptotic confidence intervals from doubly-robust estimators, or at minimum use a bias-corrected bootstrap.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      373[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  368, 374[0m:[39m[49m ```pseudocode
[0m[49m[39m  369, 375[0m:[39m[49m FUNCTION evaluate_policy_offline(policy, historical_episodes):
[0m[49m[39m  370, 376[0m:[39m[49m     // Importance-weighted evaluation (off-policy)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      377[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // NOTE: behavior_policy_prob requires a separate model of historical decisions
[0m[49m[39m  371, 378[0m:[39m[49m     results = []
[0m[49m[39m  372, 379[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  373, 380[0m:[39m[49m     FOR episode IN historical_episodes:
[0m[49m[39m  374, 381[0m:[39m[49m         cumulative_reward_policy = 0
[0m[49m[39m  375, 382[0m:[39m[49m         cumulative_reward_actual = 0
[0m[49m[39m  376, 383[0m:[39m[49m         importance_weights = []
[0m[49m[39m  377, 384[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  378, 385[0m:[39m[49m         FOR (state, actual_action, actual_reward) IN episode.transitions:
[0m[49m[39m  379, 386[0m:[39m[49m             // What would our policy have done?
[0m[49m[39m  380, 387[0m:[39m[49m             policy_action_probs = policy(state)
[0m[49m[39m  381, 388[0m:[39m[49m             policy_action = ARGMAX(policy_action_probs)
[0m[49m[39m  382, 389[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  383, 390[0m:[39m[49m             // Importance weight for off-policy correction
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 384     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m             // (only needed for full OPE; simplified here)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      391[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             // behavior_policy_prob must be estimated from a trained classifier
[0m[49m[39m  385, 392[0m:[39m[49m             weight = policy_action_probs[actual_action] / behavior_policy_prob(actual_action)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      393[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             // Clip weights to reduce variance (essential for stability)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      394[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             weight = MIN(weight, MAX_WEIGHT_CLIP)
[0m[49m[39m  386, 395[0m:[39m[49m             importance_weights.append(weight)
[0m[49m[39m  387, 396[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  388, 397[0m:[39m[49m             cumulative_reward_actual += actual_reward
[0m[49m[39m  389, 398[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  390, 399[0m:[39m[49m         // Estimate policy value using weighted importance sampling
[0m[49m[39m  391, 400[0m:[39m[49m         policy_value_estimate = WEIGHTED_IS_ESTIMATE(episode, importance_weights)
[0m[49m[39m  392, 401[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  393, 402[0m:[39m[49m         results.append({
